Click here to read this story in Spanish. With inflation rising and school starting in less than two weeks, every dollar saved on school supplies is a benefit. Multiple Florida companies and nonprofit organizations are providing them for free around Tampa Bay. Here’s where to find events — and free school supplies: St. Petersburg Junior League of St. Petersburg Back to School Care Fair: Physical and medical screenings are available as well as backpacks filled with school supplies. 8 a.m. to noon Saturday at Evara Health at Johnnie Ruth Clarke, 1344 22nd Street S., St. Petersburg. Backpacks at the Tropicana: Saturday Morning Shoppe and Live Love St. Pete are giving away 2,000 backpacks full of school supplies from 12 to 5 p.m. Aug. 6 at Tropicana Field, 1 Tropicana Drive, St. Petersburg. Learn more at livelovestpete.org and satmorningshoppe.com. Tampa 2022 Back to School Bash: Students from kindergarten through 12th grades can attend to receive a backpack full of school supplies, a physical exam and meal — all free — from 11 a.m. to 2 p.m. Friday. Event is at 7454 Palm River Road, Tampa. 813-628-9179. Future Billionaire Back 2 School Bash: Free eye exams and eyewear for children ages 5 to 17. The first 100 kids completing the scavenger hunt get a free backpack filled with school supplies. Adults in need of employment can get help applying for local job openings. From 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. Saturday. The Resource Empowerment Centre, 9309 N. Florida Ave., Tampa. 727-755-8112. Backpacks at the Raymond James: Bullard Family Foundation will celebrate the 5th Annual Back to School Bash presented by AdventHealth and Skanska at Raymond James Stadium, 4201 N. Mabry Hwy., Tampa, at 9 a.m. Aug. 6. Get a free backpack filled with school supplies and take advantage of free medical, dental and vision services, as well as complimentary haircuts, food and entertainment. Families must register for medical, dental and eye care services. To sign up, visit bit.ly/bffmedical. Families may also register for backpacks here: tinyurl.com/BASH2022BACKPACK. Back-to-School Bash: Celebration Church in Tampa will hold a Back-to-School Bash complete with bounce houses, haircuts, games and raffles as well as free backpacks for the first 200 students. 10 a.m. to 1 p.m. Saturday. Celebration Church, 16235 Lake Magdalene Blvd., Tampa (813) 961-0910. Ayr’Reka’s Angels Back to School Bash: Students can spruce up to return to class with free haircuts and braiding, HIV testing, health screenings, notary services, school supplies and a blood drive. From noon-5 p.m. Aug. 6. at 6503 N. 15th St., Tampa. 813-454-5374. Around Tampa Bay Back to School Open House and Expo: Families can visit local exhibitors providing information about school resources such as before/after school activities, health, wellness, safety and more. Kids will enjoy hands-on activities and games. The first 200 school-age children will receive a free backpack and school supplies. 6 to 8 p.m. Thursday. MLK Jr. Recreation Center, 550 Laura Lane, Dunedin. 727-738-2920. The Florida Penguin Back to School Extravaganza: Free backpacks and school supplies in Pinellas, Hillsborough and Pasco counties. The event includes 250 backpacks sponsored by Florida Penguin Productions at each location. Children can enjoy face painting and other activities. 5th Annual Back-to-School Drive: Kids Helping Kids Pasco County is at the helm of this Land O’Lakes event. Organization members will stuff and hand out backpacks to students. From 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. Saturday. Land O’Lakes Heritage Park, 5401 Land O’Lakes Blvd. (813) 957-5711. Staff writer Kelly S. Stefani contributed to this report.